ter"><img src="http://www.antique-index.com/photostore/totf/barritt.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 761<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/10/02 1:54:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2124.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Since the new AI of the caster mobs---</span><hr size=1> Nice group.<br>You have bard for crowd control and good melee power. Plus you and the bard can interupt.<br><br>If your bard has charm yet he will learn to love caster mobs <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  As a bard I could out damage anyone if I got to play with a caster mob <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>1 mob everyone fights<br>2 mobs bard either parks or charms<br>3 mobs bard can charm 1 get it to fight the other<br>4 mobs getting more uggly but there are those that can do this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Not sure about the lvl of dalnirs and you guys. Been too long since I went there <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Stick nose in and bard track <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  see if it is all red <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  If not red you guys should be fine I would recon.<br><br>Hugs<br><br>Intra and Sena <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarkitip.showPublicProfile?language=EN>arkitip</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 263<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/10/02 2:02:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2124.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Since the new AI of the caster mobs---</span><hr size=1> I've been in there recently as this group:<br><br>Warrior<br>2 Monks<br>Cleric<br><br>Then later on some others will join like:<br><br>2 SKs<br>or<br>Beastlord<br>SK<br><br>I was 26th, others in the group were 30-33.<br>We did alright because the other monk there is a pretty experienced puller. <br>As long as your monk is a good feign puller, you should be fine. If a bad pull comes along though, yeah, you'll most likely be wiped. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 762<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/10/02 2:08:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2124.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Since the new AI of the caster mobs---</span><hr size=1> They have a bard tho <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  AE mez is fun :-) or there is AE fear and leg it to the zone line <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>As for the puller, aye good pulers are a good thing.<br><br>I suggest ya put every resist ya can on the puller, and they wear any resist items they have. Dalnir has a fair number of casters and it might get ugly for them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Good luck.<br><br>Intra and Sena <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=krost>Krost</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/10/02 2:38:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2124.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Since the new AI of the caster mobs---</span><hr size=1> My usual hunting partner and I have been hunting here extensively since the new caster AI was implemented.<br><br>I am a 36 Iksar Warrior and she is a 35 Iksar Necromancer.<br><br>1st level- We own. The 2 of us easily can keep the enitre 1st level clear.<br><br>2nd level - As a duo we can hold the area with the Iksar prisoner, keeping to the exit clear and back to the &quot;Thistle lumpy&quot;<br><br>3rd Level- We hunt the area of the &quot;river&quot;. If we hold near the 2 Kly in the tents we can keep them, the goo's in the water, the Kly by the fire and the BBQ room clear, but it gets taxing after awhile.<br><br>We do better in the water just outside of the &quot;Crusader's room&quot; Sticking mainly to the goo's, the various ones that pop in the crusader room and the small chamber that is down the hall from there.<br><br><br>Things to know:<br><br>Most of the casters, while improved AI and a bit more challenging are still doable. BEWARE the Kly Invokers however. They are quite often fond of chain nuking you for over 200 a pop and their DS can rape you and not always easily dispelled.<br><br>We often avoid the Invokers if possible, we can take them out but it requires alot of health and mana to do so, leaving us weak for the next encounter.<br><br>This is still a very doable dungeon and the challenge here is indeed unique and rewarding. The 2 of us will likely stay here for quite some time.<br><br>We are going to be trying our luck at other various locations throughout the dungeon as time goes by and I'll post any relevant information<br><br>ADDED: Also, when fightig the Invokers be sure to keep you back to a wall. The distance of the knockback their spells can do is pretty large and if  you're not careful you can be knocked back into a different room filled with more Kly that  will happily beat you down.<br><br><br>Krost Gutshank<br>Skathris Ven'Sho <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=krost>Krost</A> at: 6/10/02 4:31:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubarritt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Barritt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/10/02 4:44:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2124.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Since the new AI of the caster mobs---</span><hr size=1> Krost, <br>I imagine that the Kly believers would be just as difficult as the invokers. Have you thought of the pool room on the second level by keepin the non aggro nibblers up? <br><br>We will most likely be heading there with in the next day or two since I am about 1 yeller from 30 and I wanna have my warrior smack down some giants in FM first. (This greedy lil cleric wants some earings. I feel so nekkid  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) <p><p align="center"><img src="http://www.antique-index.com/photostore/totf/barritt.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=krost>Krost</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/10/02 4:57:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2124.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Since the new AI of the caster mobs---</span><hr size=1> Actually the believers are not as difficult as I initially thought they would be, the Invokers easily outdamage them and are more difficult to take down.<br><br>Also, it has been  A LONG TIME since I last hunted Dalnir before this go around so I do not know how long this has been in effect but, Nibblers agro now and the coerced will attack and kill Goo's and nibblers. (Keep an eye on  them lumpy's people, nothing worse than to get KS'd by another mob when you trying to get some batons).<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubarritt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Barritt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/10/02 5:23:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2124.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Since the new AI of 